OFF-LIMITS.Definition: not to be interfered with, considered, or spoken of

UNCENSORED.Definition: not having any part deleted or suppressed

COMES TO MIND.Definition: to be remembered or thought of

ANTIQUATED.Definition: old-fashioned or unsuitable for modern society

ATTAIN.Definition: reach or succeed in getting something

MEANS.Definition: money or income that allows you to buy things or services

POSSESSIONS.Definition: something that you own, or the condition of owning something

PUT THE WORK IN.Definition: to apply the necessary amount of effort and labor to accomplish something

FORTUNE.Definition: prosperity attained partly through luck: success

FIRST WORLD PROBLEMS.Definition: a usually minor or trivial problem or annoyance experienced by people in relatively affluent or privileged circumstances especially as contrasted with problems of greater social significance facing people in poor and underdeveloped parts of the world

MIDDLE CLASS.Definition: a social group that consists of ordinary people who usually have good jobs and are neither rich nor very poor

MELTING POT.Definition: a place where many different people and ideas exist together, often mixing and producing something new

KEEPING UP WITH THE JONESES.Definition: to always want to own the same expensive objects and do the same things as your friends or neighbors, because you are worried about seeming less important socially than they are

KEEPING UP WITH.Definition: to do whatever is necessary to stay level or equal with someone or something

PROFESSIONS.Definition: any type of work that needs special training or a particular skill, often one that is respected because it involves a high level of education

EXACT SAME.Definition: used as a more forceful way to say same

THERAPIST.Definition: a practitioner of psychotherapy: a psychotherapist

PSYCHOLOGY.Definition: the science of mind and behavior

CLINICAL.Definition: of, relating to, or conducted in or as if in a clinic

BACKGROUND.Definition: the total of a person's experience, knowledge, and education

CREATIVE.Definition: having the quality of something created rather than imitated: imaginative

THE SHIT OUT OF.Definition: used to emphasize the degree of force of an action that you are describing

IDIOT.Definition: a stupid person or someone who is behaving in a stupid way

STATUTE OF LIMITATIONS.Definition: a law that limits the amount of time allowed to bring a legal action against someone

'NUFF SAID.Definition: there is no need to say any more; 'nuff' is an informal or dialect shortening of 'enough'

IMPRESSION.Definition: an idea or opinion of what someone or something is like

ASSUME.Definition: to accept something to be true without question or proof

DICK.Definition: a mean, stupid, or annoying man

ASSHOLE.Definition: a stupid, annoying, or detestable person

HALF-ASS.Definition: to do (something) poorly due to lack of care or effort

INVESTED.Definition: to put money, effort, time, etc. into something in order to improve it or get an advantage

DIRECT.Definition: says what they think in a very honest way without worrying about other people's opinions

SUFFER FOOLS GLADLY.Definition: to be kind to and patient with people who are annoying or bothersome —usually used in negative statements

OBLIVIOUS.Definition: lacking remembrance, memory, or mindful attention

CANCEL.Definition: to withdraw one's support for (someone, such as a celebrity, or something, such as a company) publicly and especially on social media

POLITICALLY CORRECT.Definition: conforming to a belief that language and practices which could offend political sensibilities (as in matters of sex or race) should be eliminated

COMPLAIN.Definition: to express grief, pain, or discontent

ECHO CHAMBERS.Definition: a room with sound-reflecting walls used for producing hollow or echoing sound effects —often used figuratively

LIKE MIND.Definition: (of people) sharing the same opinions, ideas, or interests

NECESSARY.Definition: needed in order to achieve a particular result

CONVERSING.Definition: to have a conversation with someone

MOB MENTALITY.Definition: the inclination that some humans have to be part of a large group, often neglecting their individual feelings in the process, and adopting the behaviors and actions of the people around them

INFLATION.Definition: a general, continuous increase in prices

EFFECTIVELY.Definition: used when you describe what the real result of a situation is

COMING TOGETHER.Definition: if people or groups come together, they join or meet in order to do something

DISAGREEING.Definition: to not have the same opinion, idea, etc.

YELLING.Definition: to shout something or make a loud noise, usually when you are angry, in pain, or excited

WHERE THEY'RE COMING FROM.Definition: the feelings someone has that cause that person to have a particular opinion

FORCING.Definition: to make something happen or make someone do something difficult, unpleasant, or unusual, especially by threatening or not offering the possibility of choice

DOOMED.Definition: certain to fail, die, or be destroyed

JUSTIFY.Definition: to prove or show to be just, right, or reasonable

WEAPONS.Definition: a means of contending against another

AT OUR DISPOSAL.Definition: available for someone to use: available for whatever one needs

NATURE.Definition: the type or main characteristic of something

PURPOSE.Definition: why you do something or why something exists

STAND UP FOR.Definition: to defend or support someone or something

INJURY.Definition: physical harm or damage to someone's body caused by an accident or an attack

ACL.Definition: anterior cruciate ligament: a cruciate ligament of each knee that attaches the front of the tibia with the back of the femur and functions especially to prevent hyperextension of the knee and is subject to injury especially by tearing
